<h3><strong>Basic Ear Massage</strong></h3>
Gently rub the outer ear using your fingers.

Use circular motions to warm up the area and stimulate blood flow.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1266" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-2024-11-26T122000.880.jpeg" alt="Ear Massage (Sense Massage Therapy)" width="267" height="178" />
<h3><strong>Pressure Points Stimulation</strong></h3>
Apply firm but gentle pressure to key points on the ear using your thumb or a reflexology tool.

Focus on areas like the lobe (linked to the head and heart) or the ridge of the ear (associated with the spine).

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1267" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-2024-11-26T125508.956.jpeg" alt="Pressure Point ( Amazon.Ae )" width="210" height="247" />

</div>
<h3><strong>Pull and Release Technique</strong></h3>
Gently pull the ear in different directions (up, down, outward) to stimulate nerves and improve circulation.

